name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: Identifiers assigned to this research study by the sponsor or other systems.

name: $addidentifier
desc: Identifiers assigned to this research study by the sponsor or other systems.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Identifiers assigned to this research study by the sponsor or other systems.

name: $title
desc: Returns: A short, descriptive user-friendly label for the study.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A short, descriptive user-friendly label for the study.

name: $protocol
desc: Returns: The set of steps expected to be performed as part of the execution of the study.

name: $addprotocol
desc: The set of steps expected to be performed as part of the execution of the study.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: The set of steps expected to be performed as part of the execution of the study.

name: $partOf
desc: Returns: A larger research study of which this particular study is a component or step.

name: $addpartOf
desc: A larger research study of which this particular study is a component or step.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: A larger research study of which this particular study is a component or step.

name: $status
desc: Returns: The current state of the study.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The current state of the study.

name: $primaryPurposeType
desc: Returns: The type of study based upon the intent of the study's activities. A classification of the intent of the study.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The type of study based upon the intent of the study's activities. A classification of the intent of the study.

name: $phase
desc: Returns: The stage in the progression of a therapy from initial experimental use in humans in clinical trials to post-market evaluation.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The stage in the progression of a therapy from initial experimental use in humans in clinical trials to post-market evaluation.

name: $category
desc: Returns: Codes categorizing the type of study such as investigational vs. observational, type of blinding, type of randomization, safety vs. efficacy, etc.

name: $addcategory
desc: Codes categorizing the type of study such as investigational vs. observational, type of blinding, type of randomization, safety vs. efficacy, etc.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Codes categorizing the type of study such as investigational vs. observational, type of blinding, type of randomization, safety vs. efficacy, etc.

name: $focus
desc: Returns: The medication(s), food(s), therapy(ies), device(s) or other concerns or interventions that the study is seeking to gain more information about.

name: $addfocus
desc: The medication(s), food(s), therapy(ies), device(s) or other concerns or interventions that the study is seeking to gain more information about.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: The medication(s), food(s), therapy(ies), device(s) or other concerns or interventions that the study is seeking to gain more information about.

name: $condition
desc: Returns: The condition that is the focus of the study.  For example, In a study to examine risk factors for Lupus, might have as an inclusion criterion "healthy volunteer", but the target condition code would be a Lupus SNOMED code.

name: $addcondition
desc: The condition that is the focus of the study.  For example, In a study to examine risk factors for Lupus, might have as an inclusion criterion "healthy volunteer", but the target condition code would be a Lupus SNOMED code.

lvardefs.desc: The condition that is the focus of the study.  For example, In a study to examine risk factors for Lupus, might have as an inclusion criterion "healthy volunteer", but the target condition code would be a Lupus SNOMED code.

name: $contact

name: $addcontact
desc: Contact details to assist a user in learning more about or engaging with the study.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Contact details to assist a user in learning more about or engaging with the study.

desc: Citations, references and other related documents.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Citations, references and other related documents.

desc: Key terms to aid in searching for or filtering the study.

lvardefs.desc: Key terms to aid in searching for or filtering the study.

desc: Indicates a country, state or other region where the study is taking place.

lvardefs.name: objRef

name: $description
desc: Returns: A full description of how the study is being conducted.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A full description of how the study is being conducted.

name: $enrollment
desc: Returns: Reference to a Group that defines the criteria for and quantity of subjects participating in the study.  E.g. " 200 female Europeans between the ages of 20 and 45 with early onset diabetes".

name: $addenrollment
desc: Reference to a Group that defines the criteria for and quantity of subjects participating in the study.  E.g. " 200 female Europeans between the ages of 20 and 45 with early onset diabetes".

lvardefs.name: objRef

desc: Returns: Identifies the start date and the expected (or actual, depending on status) end date for the study.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Identifies the start date and the expected (or actual, depending on status) end date for the study.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: An organization that initiates the investigation and is legally responsible for the study.

name: $principalInvestigator
desc: Returns: A researcher in a study who oversees multiple aspects of the study, such as concept development, protocol writing, protocol submission for IRB approval, participant recruitment, informed consent, data collection, analysis, interpretation and presentation.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A researcher in a study who oversees multiple aspects of the study, such as concept development, protocol writing, protocol submission for IRB approval, participant recruitment, informed consent, data collection, analysis, interpretation and presentation.

desc: A facility in which study activities are conducted.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: A facility in which study activities are conducted.

name: $addarm
